# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 15 (Code Quality)

Spec: `docs/17_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_15_CODE_QUALITY.md`  
Debt catalog: `docs/technical-debt.md`

## Rules

- Prefer `scripts/_test-helpers/read-source.mjs` for source-contract tests — do not duplicate `readSource`.
- Domain badges compose `StatusBadge`; compact empty panels compose `CompactEmptyState` / `EmptyState`.
- Prefer Server Components; keep `"use client"` only when required.
- New Supabase writes should use `src/lib/supabase/typed.ts` helpers when practical.
- Do not introduce `as any`, `@ts-ignore`, `TODO`, or `FIXME` in `src/`.
- Do not reintroduce Stripe packages or `/api/stripe` routes.
- Do not modify business logic, auth, RBAC, RLS, Paddle behaviour, or API contracts for cleanup convenience.
- High-risk refactors (mass `as never` removal, Stripe field renames) stay in the debt catalog — do not auto-execute.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 15 work.
